    <h1>Beef Pares</h1>
    <img src="https://thedelicious.recipes/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/beef-pares-with-fried-rice.jpg" alt="Beef pares with leeks">
    <h2>Beef Pares are cubed beef briskets cooked with spices and tenderized to perfection. 
    The aroma of this dish alone is enticing. 
    The taste is captivating. You will surely ask for more after tasting it.
    </h2>
    <h3>Ingredients</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>2 ½ lbs. beef cubed</li>
      <li>¼ cup brown sugar</li>
      <li>6 tablespoons soy sauce</li>
      <li>1 piece onion chopped</li>
      <li>5 cloves garlic crushed</li>
      <li>½ cup scallions chopped</li>
      <li>2 ½ cups water</li>
      <li>3 tablespoons cooking oil</li>
      <li>Salt and ground peppper to taste</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Steps</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Heat oil in a cooking pot or pressure cooker. Saute onion and garlic</li>
      <li>Add the beef once onion softens. Cook until light brown.</li>
      <li>Pour soy sauce and water. Stir.</li>
      <li> Cover the pressure cooker and pressure cook for 15 minutes.</li>
      <li>Add brown sugar and season with salt and ground black pepper.
          Cook for 8 to 10 minutes more or until the sauce reduces a bit.</li>
      <li>Top with chopped scallions and serve with sinangag and beef stock. Share and enjoy.</li>
    </ol>
  </body>
